A tragic shooting at a Nebraska mall left eight dead, including employees and shoppers.
The shooter, Robert A. Hawkins, had a troubled past, recently losing his job and breaking up with his girlfriend.
He left a note expressing remorse before opening fire with an assault rifle.
The community in Omaha is coming together to support each other during this difficult time.
The victims' names were released, and the injured were taken to Nebraska Medical Center.
The shooter's actions were described as random, leaving a sense of shock and sadness in the aftermath of the senseless violence.
